dius enhancement (reduced mixing),$\backslash$nand 3) increased probability of overlap in a multi-plume scheme,$\backslash$nwhere interactions benefit later generations (this part has only$\backslash$nbeen implemented in an offline toy column model). Since rain evaporation$\backslash$nis a source for org, it functions as a time-lagged but positive feedback$\backslash$non deep convection development. This evades the entrainment dilemma,$\backslash$nsince fully developed org-enhanced convection is not overly dilute,$\backslash$navoiding stability bias, while the pioneering updrafts of new convection$\backslash$nare suppressed by entrainment, encouraging more large-scale variability.},
